sentence: Among the underlying components of the Russell 3000 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in Walmart Inc (Symbol: WMT), where a total of 37,262 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 3.7 million underlying shares.
That amounts to about 48.8% of WMT's average daily trading volume over the past month of 7.6 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $90 strike call option expiring August 17, 2018 , with 6,439 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 643,900 underlying shares of WMT.

Below is a chart showing WMT's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $90 strike highlighted in orange:

Home Depot Inc (Symbol: HD) options are showing a volume of 17,396 contracts thus far today.
That number of contracts represents approximately 1.7 million underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 48.6% of HD's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 3.6 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $190 strike put option expiring August 17, 2018 , with 2,557 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 255,700 underlying shares of HD.

Below is a chart showing HD's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $190 strike highlighted in orange:

And XPO Logistics, Inc. (Symbol: XPO) saw options trading volume of 6,412 contracts, representing approximately 641,200 underlying shares or approximately 48.4% of XPO's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 1.3 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $105 strike call option expiring November 16, 2018 , with 1,519 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 151,900 underlying shares of XPO.
